This paper deals with dense semantic correspondence, which is a common problem in computer vision. The techniques presented in the paper involve optimization and regularization, which are common topics in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG and cs.AI). The paper also deals with geometric variations, which are relevant to graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM). However, the primary focus of the paper is on image analysis and processing, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV).
